UID:20241017T090000Z-007@hhfoodbank.org
CREATED:20230608T110700Z
DESCRIPTION:This will be our 40th Annual Community Book Fair. We will fill 
 two buildings with over 100\,000 books\, DVDs\, CDs\, LPs\, games\, puzzles
  and other items at affordable prices to support the food bank's work. Ther
 e will be a large selection of children's books and collectible "Better Boo
 ks\," which will also include a selection of vintage vinyl LPs. If you wish
  to donate used books CDs\, DVDs\, records\, games and puzzles at the Hoosi
 er Hills Food Bank\, do so between Monday to Friday from 9am to 5pm (2333 W
 . Industrial Park Dr). We won't accept donations of the categories above th
 e entire month of October this year\, that being from the 1st to 31st. For 
 more information regarding this please call (812) 334-8374 or email Ryan at
  volunteer@hhfoodbank.org.
LAST-MODIFIED:20240608T231831Z
LOCATION:Monroe County Fairgrounds
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:40th Annual Community Book Fair
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20231012
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20231018
DTSTAMP:20260309T020651Z
UID:0jd1v15uodug4iag167i2pu40c@google.com
CREATED:20230621T142046Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Hoosier Hills Food Bank will host the Bloomington Community 
 Book Fair October 12th-17th\, 2023 at the Monroe County Fair Grounds. The b
 ook fair features over 100\,000 items – books and much more. There are spec
 ialty areas with large collections of children’s books\, rare and collectib
 le “better books\,” horror and science fiction books\, games and puzzles\, 
 comics\, stamps and coins\, and a big media section with DVDs\, CDs\, recor
 ds\, and tapes all at great\, low prices. There will also be programs and f
 ood trucks throughout the week.</p><p>We accept gently used books\, CDs\, D
 VDs\, records\, games and puzzles at the Hoosier Hills Food Bank Monday-Fri
 day from 9 a.m.- 5 p.m (2333 W. Industrial Park Dr). We do not accept donat
 ions October 1st-31st. For more information\, please call (812) 334-8374 or
  e-mail Ryan at <a href="mailto:volunteer@hhfoodbank.org">volunteer@hhfoodb
 ank.org</a>.</p><p>We are honored to be the home of this beloved community 
 event. For more than 30 years\, we’ve promoted a message of sustainability 
 – that too much food is wasted and should instead be channeled to people at
  risk of hunger. In many ways\, the same is true of used books. We can’t af
 ford to be a throwaway society – not with food\, not with books and certain
 ly not with people.</p><p>Bring a canned food donation for a $1 book buck c
 oupon!</p><p>All proceeds benefit the programs and services of Hoosier Hill
 s Food Bank. <span>Visit our website to learn more:</span><span> </span><a 
 href="https://hhfoodbank.org/book-fair/">https://hhfoodbank.org/book-<wbr /
 >fair/</a></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230621T142058Z
LOCATION:Monroe County Fairgrounds\, 5700 W Airport Rd\, Bloomington\, IN 4
 7403 Mailing Address: 5454\, 5700 W Airport Rd\, Bloomington\, IN 47403\, U
 SA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Hoosier Hills Food Bank
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
