DESCRIPTION:<p>Unity of Bloomington welcomes Dr. Jill Bolte Taylor as she s
 peaks on "Whole Brain Living- The Anatomy of Choice and the Four Characters
  That Drive Our Life." Dr. Jill focuses on how we can activate the power of
  our neuroplasticity to not only recover from neurological trauma\, but how
  we can purposefully choose to love a more flexible\, resilient\, and satis
 fying life.</p><p>Dr. Jill is a "100 Most Influential People in the World\,
 " a premiere Guest on Oprah's "Soul Series" and her 2008 TED Talk was the f
 irst to go viral\, and currently has 28.5 million views</p>
