DESCRIPTION:Saturday Crafternoon: Crazy Quilt Stitching\n\nHave you ever se
 en a crazy quilt? Stop by the Wylie House in March to see Rebecca Wylie's 1
 00+ year-old crazy quilt\, a beautiful patchwork of fabric filled with embr
 oidery. Come to the education center and learn how to stitch those same des
 igns onto your own felt ornament.\n\nNote: March 5-7\, the Indiana Heritage
  Quilt Show will be held at the Bloomington Convention Center\, where you c
 an see contemporary quilts come to life!\n\n*The museum will be closed Satu
 rdays March 14 & 21 for Spring Break.\n\nSaturday Crafternoons are a FREE e
 vent for families\, students\, and friends of all ages! Activities change m
 onthly.\n\nContact: Kaia Wells | kaiwells@iu.edu | (812) 855-6224
