CREATED:20260102T191723Z
DESCRIPTION:Our wellbeing depends far more on the wealth we share on our pr
 ivate finances and possessions. This talk by Scott Russell Sanders\, Profes
 sor Emeritus of English at Indiana University and Fellow of the American Ac
 ademy of Arts and Sciences\, will celebrate the gifts of nature and culture
  that support and enrich our lives. It will also show how these shared rich
 es--atmosphere\, oceans\, biodiversity\, parks and public schools\, arts an
 d science\, laws and language\, and many more--are under assault by those w
 ho wish to exploit them for personal or corporate gain. By recognizing the 
 common wealth that sustains us\, we may be moved to defend it.<br><br>Offer
 ed through the<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://travelinguniv.or
 g&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AOvVaw3cZ4g4zSNZKsbd4Z
 t11gm7" target="_blank"> Traveling University</a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20260102T191723Z
LOCATION:Unitarian Universalist Church\, 2120 N Fee Ln\, Bloomington\, IN 4
 7408\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Common Wealth: Living in a Shared World
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
