UID:e1439060944316455@facebook.com
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/1439060944316455/
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260306T125958Z
DESCRIPTION:Bloomington has a special mix of people — creatives\, founders\
 , builders\, storytellers\, leaders\, students\, and neighbors. Bloomington
  Breakfast Club was created to bring those people together around real stor
 ies and meaningful work.\n\nThis monthly morning gathering is simple by des
 ign. Coffee. Conversation. Community.\n\nNo pressure. No pitch. Just a chan
 ce to start the day connected to ideas and people that matter.\n\nOur Febru
 ary Breakfast Club features Ellise A. Smith and her talk\, Threads of Resil
 ience: Reclaiming Our Stories to Build Community Connection.\n\nWhen we sha
 re our stories\, we begin to heal. When we turn those stories into art\, we
  build bridges and connection. In this interactive and deeply personal conv
 ersation\, Ellise explores how creative expression can serve as a powerful 
 tool for processing experience\, managing emotions\, and fostering meaningf
 ul connection within ourselves and our communities. Attendees will leave wi
 th new ways to think about transforming personal narratives into creative e
 xpression that supports both inner growth and collective understanding.\n\n
 About the Speaker:\n\nEllise Antoinette Smith brings an incredible depth of
  experience and passion for social justice to the spaces she occupies throu
 gh storytelling\, history\, and education. Originally from Detroit\, Michig
 an\, she is an intentional scholar-activist\, creative visionary\, and advo
 cate for historically silenced narratives\, bringing a unique interdiscipli
 nary approach to her work.\n\nThrough photography (#VisualActivism)\, podca
 sting\, spoken word poetry\, and social media\, Ellise centers the voices a
 nd experiences of communities that have historically gone unheard. As a doc
 toral student\, her academic work focuses on creating celebratory spaces fo
 r marginalized identities\, challenging dominant ideologies\, and ensuring 
 these voices are heard and valued both within and beyond academia.\n\nHer r
 ecent recognitions include the 2025 IU Indianapolis Dr. Martin Luther King 
 Persistent Pathfinder of Justice Award\, the 2025 Women’s History Month Awa
 rd\, and the 2026 American Council on Education Women’s Network Indiana Dis
 tinguished Woman Leader Award.\n\nCoffee and light breakfast provided.\nLim
 ited seating available.\n\nDoors open at 8:30am — come early\, grab coffee\
 , and meet someone new before we begin at 9:00am.\n\nRSVP here: Bloomington
  Breakfast Club: Ellise A. Smith — Threads of Resilience https://www.eventb
 rite.com/e/bloomington-breakfast-club-ellise-a-smith-threads-of-resilience-
 tickets-1982637662620?utm-campaign=social&utm-content=attendeeshare&utm-med
 ium=discovery&utm-term=listing&utm-source=wsa&aff=ebdsshwebmobile\n\nhttps:
 //www.facebook.com/events/1439060944316455/
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T130000Z
LOCATION:Lennie's
SEQUENCE:1442520
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Bloomington Breakfast Club: Ellise A. Smith — Threads of Resilience
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
