UID:immigration-politics-20251005T190000@bloomingtononline.com
CREATED:20250919T181158Z
DESCRIPTION:Immigration and deportation have been political flashpoints for
  centuries\, but these issues have been defined in very different ways by d
 ifferent groups. In this talk\, Marjorie Hershey\, Professor Emeritus of Po
 litical Science\, award-winning scholar and teacher of electoral politics\,
  will explore real facts about immigration to the US in recent decades\, th
 e widely differing ways immigration has been portrayed in American politica
 l debate\, and the consequences of those differing definitions for public p
 olicy. Join her to consider some ways to deal with the genuine economic\, c
 ultural\, and political issues of legal and undocumented immigration while 
 also coping with the emotional tone of the public discussion surrounding it
 ..\n\nReception to follow.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250919T181323Z
LOCATION:Unitarian Universalist Church\, 2120 N Fee Ln\, Bloomington\, IN 4
 7408\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Traveling University Lecture – Immigration and Politics
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
