DESCRIPTION:National Anthem: Punk Patriotism! Photography by Kathryn Coers 
 Rossman \n\nOriginally published in @polyesterzine\n\nExhibition: August 20
 25 at Backspace Gallery Bloomington \n\nOpening Reception: 08/01/25 from 5 
 to 8 PM for Gallery Walk\n\nEnter through Bonne Fête on the Courthouse Squa
 re\n\nBreak the rules. Revoke your trust in authority. We have every right 
 and\, indeed\, a duty to think independently and express suspicion and calc
 ulated disrespect. Go punk!\n\nPhotographer Kathryn Coers Rossman is a prou
 d patriot\, 100 percent hoodlum and product of American decline. She channe
 ls her cultural unease about American identity into this project\, aiming t
 o reclaim the flag for those who feel alienated from it.\n\nThe artist enga
 ges political surrealism as a means to reflect on civil discourse and civic
  identity.\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/events/707017898904926/
LAST-MODIFIED:20250716T012908Z
LOCATION:Backspace Gallery
SEQUENCE:4346
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:National Anthem: Punk Patriotism! Photography by Kathryn Coers Ross
 man 
