UID:1nkkv7oc4quoqmepjuh7pu2ivt@google.com
CREATED:20230708T144833Z
DESCRIPTION:<h2>Mending Day is the second Saturday of each month\, noon til
 l 4PM. Join our sewing circle as we teach\, learn\, help others\, mend and 
 create art.<br>Please be kind and pre-launder your projects.<br></h2><br>Br
 ing your sewing\, interest in sewing\, interest to learn\, and willingness 
 to teach\, or just bring pre-washed fabric items in need of mending or alte
 ration! We fix and alter garments and other fabric items for free\, as a se
 rvice to the greater community\, for fun! Let’s keep things useful and out 
 of landfill together!<h2><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.
 bloomingtonvolunteernetwork.org/need/detail/?need_id%3D355829&amp\;sa=D&amp
 \;source=calendar&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AOvVaw3EzRHKM1FFCzDTiJ_963K2" target=
 "_blank">Calling all Artists\, Fashion Designers\, Creatives\, and Communit
 y Members of All Ages Interested in Sustainable Practices. </a></h2><p></p>
 <p>Discardia\, a program of the Center for Sustainable Living\, creates an 
 environment for local designers to brainstorm to make upcycled clothing and
  to teach people in the community how to upcycle their own items. </p><h3>G
 et involved with Discardia as a Mending Day Sewing Advisor: <a href="https:
 //www.google.com/url?q=https://www.bloomingtonvolunteernetwork.org/need/det
 ail/?need_id%3D355829&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AO
 vVaw3EzRHKM1FFCzDTiJ_963K2" target="_blank">https://www.bloomingtonvoluntee
 rnetwork.org/need/detail/?need_id=355829</a></h3><p>Discardia members and v
 olunteer Sewing Advisors assist attendees in mending clothing\, giving them
  an opportunity to learn how to sew or work on any other project involving 
 clothing. Sewing machines and basic supplies are provided to participants\,
  for free\, and all ages are welcome!</p><p>Volunteer Sewing Advisors offer
  help to participants with altering or repairing the garments that they hav
 e brought in. Use your skills to assist participants with creative solution
 s\, but not to make all the decisions for them.</p><p>Help is also apprecia
 ted in setting up and tearing down before and after the event (30 minutes e
 ach). </p><p>This is a great way to empower as well as collaborate with a g
 roup of creative problem solvers and learn to use the various tools and tri
 cks of the trade to make it easier to make adjustments to our own clothes s
 o that they fit well and are comfortable and we feel good wearing them.</p>
 <p>All skill levels are welcome and training is provided. It&#39\;s a lot o
 f fun and makes you feel empowered and confident. <span>Contact Stephen Hal
 e\, Discardia Project Manager if interested at 812-334-0922.</span></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230708T144833Z
LOCATION:Monroe County Public Library - Downtown\, 303 E Kirkwood Ave\, Blo
 omington\, IN 47408\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Discardia Mending Day
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
