DTEND:20250927T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020651Z
UID:5qli3hvukjqjk021tirb6jith3@google.com
CREATED:20250826T162919Z
DESCRIPTION:Makevention is an exhibit and celebration of the maker spirit i
 n Bloomington. Come see the inventive and creative passions of your communi
 ty!\n\nMaker culture includes a wide range of activities\, including 3D pri
 nting\, textiles\, woodworking\, and games. It unites people from various b
 ackgrounds\, from home-based inventors to production companies\, who like t
 o build things and embrace problem solving\, transforming ideas into tangib
 le forms.\n\nIn many ways\, Bloomington\, Indiana is the perfect community 
 to showcase the maker movement. There is\, of course\, a large art communit
 y using digital fabrication\, 3D printers\, screen printing\, laser cutters
 \, CNCs\, and loads of other innovative art techniques. There is also an in
 terest in recycling and “upcycling” as Bloomingtonians have a drive to redu
 ce waste and live intentionally. And being a college town\, as a community 
 we love to learn\, explore\, build\, and make.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250826T162936Z
LOCATION:1601 S Rogers St\, Bloomington\, IN 47403\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Makevention
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
