UID:e1229908412448081@facebook.com
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/1229908412448081/
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260306T125957Z
DESCRIPTION:As the land begins to wake up and the wildflowers bloom\, it’s 
 time for us to come together once again. We are thrilled to invite you to o
 ur 9th annual Spring Gathering\, a four-day immersive celebration of music\
 , art\, and the spirit of community.\n\nThis isn't just a festival\; it’s a
  transformative experience where we bridge the gap between artist and obser
 ver\, neighbor and friend. Whether you are here for the workshops\, the mus
 ic\, or the simple peace of camping under the stars\, there is a place for 
 you here.\n\nWhat to expect:\n\nWe begin Friday night with an opening fire 
 circle and informal jam sessions. Feel free to bring your instruments and p
 lay around the fireside\, or simply just vibe.\n\nCreate & Learn: Dive into
  workshops led by incredible talent\, including painting\, flow arts\, drum
 ming\, and storytelling.\n\nEnjoy diverse live performances from local and 
 traveling musicians throughout the weekend.\n\nFamily Magic: From the Mysti
 cal March costume parade and the Kid's Glow Party to the Sunday Variety Sho
 w\, our Kid Village is designed to spark wonder in our youngest community m
 embers.\n\nA Gathering for Everyone\nIn keeping with our values of inclusio
 n and accessibility\, this event is donation-based with free camping. We be
 lieve that financial barriers should never stand in the way of cultural con
 nection. \n\nIt is our team of dedicated volunteers and donors who keep thi
 s space running\, so there are many ways to get involved including musical 
 performances\, workshop leadership\, vending\, and more in exchange for adm
 ission.\n\n\n🎶 Stage Request Form: \nhttps://forms.gle/p6BN9YxxisC1yf7L6\n
 \n🛍️ Vendors: \nhttps://forms.gle/sw819oxZACBv4yCu5\n\n🤸🏽‍♂️Workshop Lea
 ders:\nhttps://forms.gle/TDpvNbFitqtkmqXN6\n\n🤹‍♀️ Children's Playshop Lea
 ders:  \nhttps://forms.gle/YztG9Q4vHxqWqMHB8\n\n👐 Volunteer Request Form: 
 \nhttps://forms.gle/EV4nnrPPnN3ZCGCcA\n\n\nALL individuals 16+ must fill ou
 t a Registration Form in order to enter the event. There will be a device a
 t the gate to fill it out upon arrival\, a QR code to scan to fill it out o
 n your own device\, or you can fill it out now to save some time once you a
 rrive! \n\nEveryone will need to fill this out regardless if you are a volu
 nteer\, a vendor\, resident\, stage artist\, have attended events at Sage V
 alley before\, or any other circumstance. This is NOT the same as the other
  links above! We must have one completed for ALL event attendees in additio
 n to your ticket\, volunteer\, stage\, and/or vendor form. \n\n✍️ Registrat
 ion Form: https://forms.gle/T4xqrEE2RXc9tVLC6\n\n\nThis gathering is hosted
  by Sage Valley\, a 501(c)3 non-profit organization. All proceeds go toward
 s creating the event and growing the projects and programs at Sage Valley! 
 Donations of time\, resources\, or monetary energy beyond the suggested don
 ation are encouraged. \n\nSuggested donation to camp at this event is on a 
 sliding scale of $30-$100 per adult or family\, in addition to one or more 
 items to donate to our vegan kitchen\, which provides free meals throughout
  the event. \n\nChildren 15 years old and under require NO admission donati
 on. Minors must be accompanied by a legal guardian. \n\nWe do accept altern
 atives to monetary donations\, here's our list of acceptable donation items
 : https://docs.google.com/document/d/1lXlLmt3BiOfK6FckOlQ8j5zSouwGEaDCURkqN
 _Mzivs/edit?usp=sharing\n\n\n\nFAQ\n----------\n➸11:11 MEETINGS\nOn Friday\
 , Saturday\, and Sunday there will be a community-wide meeting at 11:11 am!
  This is the time to receive all the information you need to make your expe
 rience as wonderful as possible. Please aim to attend daily to stay updated
  on the day's flow\, ask questions\, offer your input\, and get to know our
  team and community members! \n\n\n➸GATE HOURS\nThe gate officially opens a
 t 10AM on Friday\, May 1st. ((Early entry will ONLY be allowed for register
 ed and pre-approved volunteers.)) The gate will be closed at 9PM each night
  to ensure safety. Entry after 9PM will not be permitted. \n\nDRIVE SLOWLY 
 when approaching the gate\, the road is curved at the gate entry and on a h
 ill!\n\n\n➸WHY MONETARY DONATION? WHY FOOD DONATION?\n\nAdmission and kitch
 en donations ensure we are all giving what we can. As a nonprofit\, No prof
 its are taken from donations. Donations go into creating the most magical g
 atherings we can now and in the future. Hosting a gathering of this magnitu
 de takes resources and funding. Our goal is to provide as much as we can in
  a sustainable way. Donations can be made online and at the gate.\n\nEveryo
 ne entering the event grounds will need to give a donation of money\, time\
 , or accepted food to the community. If you find the suggested minimum dona
 tion unaffordable\, there are volunteer opportunities and other creative al
 ternative donations for admission. \n\n\nIMPORTANT NOTE: ALL ONLINE DONATIO
 NS ARE FINAL\, NON-REFUNDABLE\, & NON-RETURNABLE. \n\n\nBy donating you und
 erstand & agree to all the information provided on the donation/ticket webs
 ite. Tickets are transferable & you are encouraged to gift your ticket if c
 ircumstances shift and you're unable to attend.\n\n➸CAMPING\, RVs & BUSES\n
 This are NO hookups available at Sage Valley. \n\nThere are designated spac
 es spaces for RVs\, busses\, and Vans. They'll be pointed out to you join a
 rrival!\n\n➸CAMPING\nSage Valley is off-grid and camping is PRIMITIVE. Plea
 se plan accordingly. There are several options for your camping experience 
 including areas for car camping\, tent camping\, family camping\, & forest 
 camping. (Forest camping requires all gear to be hiked in as it is not acce
 ssible by vehicles. If you need help with transporting gear\, we have a UTV
  and may be able to help! Just let those at gate check-in know.)\n\n\n➸FOOD
  AND WATER\nSage Valley's vegan kitchen will provide plant based meals thro
 ughout the weekend! You're welcome to bring in additional food for nourishm
 ent between provided meals. Though wildlife is minimal during gathering sea
 son\, please prepare as if you were camping anywhere outdoors. If you need 
 advice on how to store your food\, let someone know! \n\nYou may use a smal
 l camp stove at your campsite. You may NOT build a fire at your campsite un
 less there is a fire pit already present when you arrive. You may NOT cook 
 at the sacred fire. If you need a fire for cooking please let someone know 
 and we will show you where to go!\n\nSage Valley's water is pumped from the
  well underneath the land and filtered for our drinking. You're encouraged 
 to bring your own water in addition! \n\n➸DRIVING/PARKING DURING EVENT\nVie
 w our Driving/Parking Policy here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/15Qon
 FI5hLlNJzZVp933DeYyaUrGZs8gOzNg14hh2ePI/edit?usp=sharing. \n\n\n➸VENDORS\nC
 ome one and come all vendors! We encourage vending of your DIY and homemade
  crafts\, art\, services\, foods\, and more! If you are interested in vendi
 ng\, please register here so that we may plan the space accordingly and hav
 e a spot reserved for you: https://forms.gle/6kiQoDN4h3eM6BLH9\n\n\n\n➸SECU
 RITY & SAFETY\nThis is primarily a self-regulated event where attendees are
  expected to speak out and stand up for what is right. Appointed Peace Keep
 ers will be available throughout the event to promote safety. We take care 
 of each other and strive to create a safe space for all! Please be sure to 
 respect and listen to one another.\n\n\n➸HANDICAP ACCESSIBILITY\nWe do ever
 ything we can to make this event as accessible as possible to all. Parking 
 is within walking distance from the main event area\, however\, the terrain
  is naturally very uneven. If you have any special needs to be considered\,
  please reach out to the event organizers so that we may try our best to ac
 commodate you.\n\n\n➸LEAVE-NO-TRACE\nThis is a LEAVE-NO-TRACE event! It's s
 imple: leave the place you camp the same or better than you found it. Pack 
 it in and pack it out. This property is an actual ecovillage where people l
 ive. Please treat it the way you would want others to treat your own home. 
 If you see others not honoring the LEAVE-NO-TRACE motto\, take some time to
  explain to them why it's important & nicely ask them to pick up after them
 selves. All trash brought onto the land must be carried off of the land. Tr
 ash removal costs money & uses resources\, energy\, and time. Attendees fou
 nd disrupting the natural beauty of the land will be prompt
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T130000Z
LOCATION:9975 N State Rd 67\, Worthington\, IN\, United States\, Indiana 47
 471
SEQUENCE:604867
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Awakening Earth: A Spring Arts Gathering at Sage Valley
TRANSP:OPAQUE
