DESCRIPTION:POSTPONED due to weather to February 8 at 3:00 and 5:00. \n\nJo
 in Voces Novae chamber choir for another one of our explorations of Indiana
  History. This program will look at the "Moon Shot" through the story of as
 tronaut Gus Grissom\, a native of Mitchell.\n\nHow do we even imagine such 
 a goal? And how many details need to line up to accomplish it? Another Hoos
 ier\, mathematician Margaret Hamilton developed the "human-in-the-loop" dec
 ision capability software that helped make it possible. With music by David
  Bowie\, Laura Farnell\, Meredith Monk\, Jacob Narverud\, Jacques Offenbach
 \, Giovanni Palestrina\, Andrea Ramsey\, and Richard Strauss. Featuring han
 dmade crankies by Sam Bartlett.\n\nTwo FREE performances at 3:00 and 5:00 p
 m on Sunday\, February 8 at the Unitarian Universalist Church of Bloomingto
 n\, IN. Donations accepted at the door. The concert will last just under an
  hour. Come join us\, whether you've never heard Voces Novae before or are 
 a lifetime groupie!\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/events/872517098643306/
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T130000Z
LOCATION:Unitarian Universalist Church of Bloomington\, 2120 N Fee Ln
SEQUENCE:4297847
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:To the moon! A choral concert by Voces Novae
TRANSP:OPAQUE
