UID:switchyard-tactile-map-20250613@bloomingtonparks
CREATED:20250604T192023Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>🎉 <strong>Celebrate a Milestone in Accessibility at Switchy
 ard Park!</strong></p><p>Join Bloomington Parks and Recreation on <strong>T
 hursday\, June 13 at 12:00 PM</strong> for the unveiling of the city's <str
 ong>first tactile map</strong>\, specially designed for park visitors who a
 re blind or have low vision. This durable\, outdoor map features raised tex
 tures\, braille labels\, and high color contrast to help everyone explore S
 witchyard Park with greater confidence and independence.</p><p>The event wi
 ll be held <strong>next to the Pavilion and the B-Line Trail</strong> in be
 autiful Switchyard Park (<strong>1601 S Rogers St\, Bloomington\, IN 47403<
 /strong>). <a>📍 View on Google Maps</a></p><p><strong>Mayor Kerry Thomson<
 /strong> will speak\, along with members of the <strong>Council for Communi
 ty Accessibility</strong> and Parks and Recreation staff\, as they highligh
 t this important step toward a more inclusive park system.</p><p>This tacti
 le map is just one part of the city’s broader accessibility initiative\, su
 pported by nearly $1 million in American Rescue Plan funding. Other recent 
 improvements include wheelchair-accessible transportation\, inclusive playg
 rounds\, and new ADA-compliant features across several park locations.</p><
 p>No registration is needed — just show up and help us celebrate progress t
 oward a more inclusive Bloomington.</p><p>♿ <strong>All are welcome.</stron
 g> Accessible parking is available near the Pavilion.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250620T133341Z
LOCATION:Switchyard Park\, 1601 S Rogers St\, Bloomington\, IN 47403\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Switchyard Park Tactile Map Unveiling
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
