CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260306T125958Z
DESCRIPTION:Over 40 million people in America receive SNAP (food stamp) ben
 efits\, over 70 million are enrolled in Medicaid\, and about 9 million rece
 ive Section 8 Housing Vouchers. Gerhard Glomm\, Professor of Economics\, wi
 ll discuss some of the design features of these programs\, with an emphasis
  on relatively recent changes such as work requirements. He will then share
  data on the costs and benefits of these programs. This event will be held 
 at the Brown County Public Library\, 205 Locust Lane\, Nashville\, IN.\n\nh
 ttps://www.facebook.com/events/25935694006040900/
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T130000Z
LOCATION:Brown County Public Library
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Some Economics of the Social Safety Net
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
