DTEND:20260207T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020651Z
UID:e1208977610564704@facebook.com
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/1208977610564704/
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260306T125957Z
DESCRIPTION:Almost since its inception\, PBS has been a political football.
  Even so it continues to be one of the most trusted institutions in America
 . But even many of PBS's champions do not know where PBS came from\, how it
  is structured\, or how it is funded. Steve Krahnke\, former Senior Lecture
 r in the Indiana University Media School\, 30-year veteran of PBS stations 
 and program production\, and executive producer of the award-winning Cuba: 
 The Forgotten Revolution\, provides some clarity. \n\nhttps://www.facebook.
 com/events/1208977610564704/
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T130000Z
LOCATION:Brown County Public Library
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:PBS: A Legacy of Service
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
