DESCRIPTION:The Bloomington Garden Club has cultivated a vibrant community 
 centered around a shared love for gardening and commitment to civic plantin
 g and beautification since 1938. Hosting the annual Garden Walk is the prim
 ary way the club fulfills its philanthropic responsibility to stimulate kno
 wledge and love for gardening\, aid in the protection of natives trees\, pl
 ants and birds\, and encourage civic beautification. All money from ticket 
 sales goes to grants in the Monroe County community that further the club's
  mission. This year six private gardens will be featured: three are in Old 
 Historic Bloomington and provide a walkable tour\, and three although close
  together are drivable or bikeable.<br><br><a href="https://bloomingtongard
 enclub.org/">https://bloomingtongardenclub.org/</a><br><h1>2024 Garden Walk
  Ticket Vendors<br><hr /></h1><br><p><em><i>All tickets are $10 per person.
 </i></em> </p><p>Children under 12 are free. Each person over age 12 enteri
 ng a garden needs a ticket.   <br><br>You may purchase tickets at any of th
 e following locations beginning May through June 23: </p><p></p><ul><li><st
 rong><b>Bloomingfoods East </b></strong>3220 East Third Street\, 812-336-54
 00</li><li><strong><b>Bloomingfoods West </b></strong>316 West Sixth Street
 \, 812-333-7312</li><li><strong><b>Bloomington Farm Stop Collective </b></s
 trong>902 W Kirkwood Avenue\, 812-369-4330 </li><li><strong><b>Bloomington 
 Hardware </b></strong>2700 East Covenanter Drive\, 812-339-7575</li><li><st
 rong><b>Bloomington Valley Nursery </b></strong>5230 Old State Road 37\, 81
 2-824-8813</li><li><strong><b>Ellettsville True Value Hardware\, Ellettsvil
 le IN </b></strong>4610 West Richland Plaza\, 812-876-2632</li><li><strong>
 <b>Goods for Cooks </b></strong>115 N College Avenue\, 812-339-2200</li><li
 ><strong><b>Hall's Greenhouse </b></strong>4855 S. Harmony Road\, 812-825-7
 070</li><li><strong><b>Mays Greenhouse </b></strong>6280 South Old State Ro
 ad 37\, 812-824-8630</li><li><strong><b>Morgenstern’s Bookstore &amp\; Cafe
  </b></strong>849 S Auto Mall Road\, 812-676-7323 </li></ul><p></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20240524T150305Z
LOCATION:Six private gardens
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Bloomington Garden Walk
TRANSP:OPAQUE
