UID:2i63mj9vooc0ms630uo9qr58q0@google.com
CREATED:20230216T171637Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>City of Bloomington Mayor John Hamilton encourages all commu
 nity members to nominate outstanding volunteers for the Be More Awards\, th
 e community volunteer awards presented by the City of Bloomington Volunteer
  Network\, a program of the City of Bloomington Community and Family Resour
 ces Department. Nominations are being accepted through March 5\, 2023\, at 
 <a href="https://www.bloomingtonvolunteernetwork.org/bemore"><u>https://www
 .bloomingtonvolunteernetwork.org/bemore</u></a><strong><b><br></b></strong>
 </p><p><strong><b>This year's award categories are\;</b></strong></p><ul><l
 i><strong><b>Be More Bloomington Award\,</b></strong> presented to an indiv
 idual or group demonstrating excellence in response to issues of 2022. Hous
 ing/homelessness\, justice\, and post-COVID recovery are examples of 2022 i
 ssues.</li><li><strong><b>Be More Creative Award</b></strong>\, honoring vo
 lunteer work within the arts community.</li><li><strong><b>Be More Dedicate
 d Award</b></strong>\, presented to an individual or couple over the age of
  60 for their lifetime of service within the community.</li><li><strong><b>
 Be More Energized Award</b></strong>\, honoring an individual or group unde
 r the age of 25.</li><li><strong><b>Be More Engaged Award</b></strong>\, ho
 noring engagement professionals working with a volunteer program within an 
 organization or business.</li><li><strong><b>Be More Impactful Award</b></s
 trong>\, honoring the volunteer or volunteer group of the year.</li><li><st
 rong><b>Be More Phenomenal Award</b></strong>\, presented to outstanding le
 adership through board\, commission\, or committee involvement.</li></ul><p
 ><strong><b>Each of the seven Be More Award recipients will receive a $1\,0
 00 cash award provided by Community Foundation of Bloomington and Monroe Co
 unty for the recipient's nonprofit organization in honor of their outstandi
 ng service. 2023 Be More Award recipients will be honored in a celebration 
 ceremony on <strong><b>April 13th</b></strong> at the Whikeart Auditorium l
 ocated in the newly remodeled John Waldron Arts Center Auditorium.</b></str
 ong></p><p><strong><b>Nominations can be submitted between now and March 5t
 h\, 2023. </b></strong></p><p>*For anyone having difficulty accessing the o
 nline form\, or who needs assistance please reach out to Michelle Moss at 8
 12-349-3433 or getconnected@bloomington.in.gov</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230216T171637Z
LOCATION:https://www.bloomingtonvolunteernetwork.org/bemore
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Be More Awards - Nominate a Community Volunteer
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
