UID:5736id7bshnp9sheskhqaa0m72@google.com
CREATED:20260207T144001Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>WISDOM OF HAPPINESS</strong></p><p>From executive pr
 oducers Richard Gere and Oren Moverman\, <strong>Wisdom of Happiness</stron
 g> offers a powerful message of hope in uncertain times.</p><p>In an intima
 te\, direct address to viewers\, Nobel Peace Prize winner <strong>Tenzin Gy
 atso</strong>\, known worldwide as the Dalai Lama\, shares practical wisdom
  on cultivating peace\, compassion\, and happiness amid modern challenges. 
 Speaking to our shared global community\, he reflects on overcoming negativ
 e emotions\, strengthening love and kindness\, and recognizing the deep int
 erconnectedness of humanity.</p><p>The film is a visually rich\, immersive 
 experience that explores how inner calm can help us respond to daily stress
 \, climate anxiety\, and global conflict with clarity and care. The Dalai L
 ama also emphasizes the urgent need for compassion and connection\, suggest
 ing that feminine wisdom and leadership will play a vital role in shaping a
  more harmonious future.</p><p>At 90 years old\, the Dalai Lama looks back 
 on a remarkable life of spiritual leadership and invites us all to imagine 
 and help create a world where happiness is truly within reach for everyone.
 </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260207T144555Z
LOCATION:Buskirk-Chumley Theater\, 114 E Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47
 408\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Wisdom of Happiness (2025)
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20230907T223000Z
DTEND:20230908T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260309T020651Z
UID:7f5q6bp8n1t9kj136dg0oii5sr@google.com
CREATED:20230811T152719Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Indiana Humanities is hosting a multi-city film tour for the
  brand-new film\, <i><i>Liminal: Indiana in the Anthropocene</i></i>. <i><i
 >Liminal </i></i>is a meditative aerial film that illustrates our state as 
 a microcosm of this new planetary epoch. It captures features of this globa
 l phenomenon within the boundaries of our state\, collapsing the global int
 o the local. This event is part of the Unearthed initiative\, Indiana Human
 ities’ multiyear environmental theme that asks Hoosiers to consider how we 
 affect the environment and how the environment affects us. </p><p>See the t
 railer here: <a href="http://liminalmovie.com/">http://liminalmovie.com/</a
 >. </p><p><b>SCHEDULE<br></b>6:00 PM Doors open (Please note: early entry w
 ill not be permitted)<br>6:30 PM Film screening begins<br>7:30 PM Film scre
 ening ends / Q&amp\;A begins<br>8:00 PM Q&amp\;A concludes</p><p><b>ABOUT T
 HE FILM<br></b><i><i>Liminal: Indiana in the Anthropocene</i></i> (54 minut
 es) is a meditative aerial film that illustrates our state as a microcosm o
 f this new planetary epoch. Society is accelerating into the Anthropocene w
 here our relationship with the Earth is one of conquest\, dominance\, and m
 anipulation. This new epoch encapsulates the world as human civilization fu
 ndamentally distorts ecological and planetary systems. It is incessant and 
 expansive motion\, a profound generation of power\, endless extraction\, an
 d nonstop movement of materials all fed into a global metabolism. The bypro
 duct is continuous dumping\, pollution\, and transformation. And yet\, enca
 sed within the Anthropocene’s vast tentacles\, we find it difficult to comp
 rehend the unnerving transitions of this new world. The immensity of the An
 thropocene’s broad signatures that span continents make it both ubiquitous 
 and opaque. What if we could compress it into a defined space to better vis
 ualize and perceive it globally and locally? </p><p><i><i>Liminal</i></i> c
 aptures features of this global phenomenon within the boundaries of our sta
 te\, collapsing the global into the local. We present the world of the Anth
 ropocene not as an exotic feature of a transformed landscape on the other s
 ide of the world\, but in a space we inhabit\; our home\, Indiana. The Anth
 ropocene isn’t “out there” but “right here”.</p><p>Entirely filmed with dro
 ne cameras by Indiana Aerials and accompanied by an original score written 
 by Ft. Wayne composer Nate Utesch of Metavari\, Liminal reveals a compellin
 g and uncanny view of Indiana in all its features and forms. </p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20230811T152719Z
LOCATION:Buskirk-Chumley Theater\, 114 E Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47
 408\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:LIMINAL: INDIANA IN THE ANTHROPOCENE
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
