UID:groups-collective-opening@picturagallery.com
CREATED:20250601T183852Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Join us for the opening night of the <em>Groups Coll
 ective</em> exhibition</strong> by acclaimed European photographers <strong
 >Jon Tonks</strong> (UK) and <strong>Roman Franc</strong> (Czech Republic) 
 — the first U.S. city project of its kind — hosted at <a href="https://pict
 uragallery.com/">Pictura Gallery</a> in Bloomington\, Indiana.</p><p>📷 <em
 >Groups Collective</em> is a global portrait series celebrating community i
 dentity through large-scale group photographs. For the Bloomington edition\
 , Tonks and Franc photographed local groups — including firefighters\, Litt
 le 500 cyclists\, ballet students\, quarry workers\, artists\, and more — t
 o create a visual story of civic life.</p><p>🎉 <strong>Event Highlights</s
 trong></p><ul><li><p>Opening Reception: <strong>Friday\, June 6 | 5:00–9:00
  PM</strong></p></li><li><p>Part of <strong>Bloomington Gallery Walk</stron
 g> and the <strong>6th Annual Fourth and Rogers Block Party</strong></p></l
 i><li><p>📸 <em>Final community group portrait</em> will be taken during th
 e event</p></li><li><p>🎶 Live music\, 🍽️ food trucks\, 🖼️ local art vend
 ors</p></li><li><p>FREE &amp\; open to the public!</p></li></ul><p>📍 <stro
 ng>Location:</strong><br>Pictura Gallery at FAR Center for Contemporary Art
 s<br><strong>202 S. Rogers Street\, Bloomington\, IN 47404</strong><br><a>
 📍 View on Google Maps</a></p><p>👥 All portrait participants and the gener
 al public are warmly invited!</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250620T133341Z
LOCATION:FAR Center for Contemporary Arts\, 202 S Rogers St\, Bloomington\,
  IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Groups Collective Opening & Fourth and Rogers Block Party
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
