DESCRIPTION:Love is in the air for all! Celebrate friendship\, community\, 
 and human connection of all kinds this February at Love at the Museum. Brin
 g a friend\, partner\, or relative and join the Museum for an early Valenti
 ne’s (or Palentine’s!) celebration that’s all about togetherness.\n\nEnjoy 
 our free\, fully-stocked chocolate and beverage bar  while listening to a w
 onderful violin and cello duo from the Jacobs School of Music. Then\, get c
 reative with crafts: make your own luminaries\, paint your own wax melts\, 
 craft custom holiday cards\, and compose unique newspaper poetry. Last but 
 not least\, check out a variety of Valentine’s themed items from the collec
 tions stewarded by the Museum!\n\nWe can't wait to see you at this lovely a
 nd uplifting February program. (We'll all need the morale boost to make it 
 through this winter!)\n\nFree & Open to All\n\nParking Information:\n\nLimi
 ted complimentary parking is available in front of the museum entrance off 
 Indiana Avenue. Street parking is free on weekdays after 5:00 PM in the nei
 ghborhoods surrounding the Museu​m. \n\nPaid parking options include the Mc
 Calla Building lot off Indiana Avenue\, the Indiana Memorial Union lots\, a
 nd the Poplars Parking Garage. Metered street parking is also available in 
 the downtown/Sample Gates area\, along Kirkwood Avenue\, East 6th Street\, 
 East 4th Street\, North Lincoln Street\, North Dunn Street\, and South Gran
 t Street.\n\nQuestions?\n\nFor accessibility assistance or questions about 
 this event\, please reach out to Camden Hill at camrhill@iu.edu or (812) 85
 5-1696.\n\nNote:\n\nBy attending this event\, you agree to be in photograph
 y that may be used by the University for promotional purposes. If you would
  not like to be in any pictures\, please speak to a Museum staff member and
  they will inform assigned photographers of your request. If you see that y
 our image has been used in error\, please reach out to iumaa@iu.edu to requ
 est that it be taken down.\n\nhttps://www.facebook.com/events/1205147815126
 067/
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T130000Z
LOCATION:416 N Indiana Ave\, Bloomington\, IN\, United States\, Indiana 474
 08
SEQUENCE:1003
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Love at the Museum
